{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MzczODc1NTAx", "number": 169, "title": "Improve Code Formatting", "bodyText": "See #130\nCurrent state of affairs:\n\n\n\u2714\ufe0f make //@formatter:off before each stream pipeline unnecessary\n~> there's a magic value (two actually, 80 is ok as well) - they correspond to Line Wrapping ~> Wrapping Settings ~> Function Calls ~> Qualified Invocations in Eclipse's formatter settings.\n<setting id=\"org.eclipse.jdt.core.formatter.alignment_for_selector_in_method_invocation\" value=\"48\"/>\n\n\n\n\u2714\ufe0f disable star imports\n~> not governed by the formatter, so we created a Checkstyle rule for it:\nmodule name=\"AvoidStarImport\" />\n\n\n\n\u2714\ufe0f enforce empty lines at start and end of class\n~> thanks to Bug 169131 getting fixed after 13 years, add:\n<setting id=\"org.eclipse.jdt.core.formatter.blank_lines_before_first_class_body_declaration\" value=\"1\"/>\n<setting id=\"org.eclipse.jdt.core.formatter.blank_lines_after_last_class_body_declaration\" value=\"1\"/>\n\n\n\n\u2714\ufe0f in if, closing } and else on the same line\n~> add:\n<setting id=\"org.eclipse.jdt.core.formatter.insert_new_line_before_else_in_if_statement\" value=\"do not insert\"/>\n\n\n\n\u2714\ufe0f make sure line continuations are indented twice (see, e.g. SystemPropertyExtension)\n~> looks like a brain fart on my end; everything seems to be ok\n\n\n\nI hereby agree to the terms of the JUnit Pioneer Contributor License Agreement.", "createdAt": "2020-02-11T20:54:08Z", "url": "https://github.com/junit-pioneer/junit-pioneer/pull/169", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "c8a82b255175c3e568ae32a69276a04a04ff44ce"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-02-18T18:37:12Z", "author": {"login": "nipafx"}, "timelineItems": {"totalCount": 6, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABcDXSG5gH2gAyMzczODc1NTAxOjFiNzE3Mzk4MzRkZWI3MTk3YTYyYTdlOGEyZTBjM2YzMjBmMGJhNjk=", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABcFmxo_gFqTM2MDU5NjYxMQ==